  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity Surveyor",
  "description": "<h5>Job Description &amp; Requirements</h5>\n<p><strong>Sucessful Candiate should possess the following:</strong></p>\n<p>Degree in Quantity Surveying or related discipline with minimum 3 years experience in as QS in Interior fit out / building industry.</p>\n<p><strong>The Job:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage Pre-tender to post-contract stages include procurement administration for projects.</li>\n  <li>Taking off quantities, read specifications and interpret construction drawings and prepare project budget and recommend to Management for acceptance of contract value for tender submission.</li>\n  <li>Responsible for vetting, drafting and negotiation of contract terms including pricing, quantity, management of vendor and sub-contractor. Ability to identify potential contract conflicts or technical issues and propose sound solutions.</li>\n  <li>Must be resourceful in sourcing of materials, vendors and sub-contractors to meet the specification and schedule. Ability to evaluate and negotiate prices is an added advantage.</li>\n  <li>Attend site show round, carry out site survey where necessary as well as attending tender interview.</li>\n  <li>Control and monitor work process, procedures and ensure policy are in order so as to achieve productivity, timely delivery and acceptable standards.</li>\n  <li>Project administration and documentation including preparation of interim valuations, pricing and agreement of contract variations, update claim submission and follow up with payment response.</li>\n  <li>Determine final costs and variation orders as well as preparing final accounts for submission to client.</li>\n  <li>Evaluation, certification and settlement of final cost with vendors&amp; sub-contractors.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The Person:·</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/Degree in Quantity Surveying or related discipline.</li>\n  <li>Minimum of 3 years of working experience as QS in Interior fit-out / building industry.</li>\n  <li>Independent, highly self-motivated, proactive and detailed with excellent problem solving skills.</li>\n  <li>Good team player and adaptable to a dynamic environment</li>\n  <li>Good communication &amp; interpersonal skills, able to interact with people of all levels.</li>\n  <li>Independent and Confident to meet tight deadlines</li>\n  <li>May require to travel overseas when required</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and AutoCAD</li>\n</ul>",
